-- Ocampo Withdraws From World Bank Contest, Portafolio Reports
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-04-13T20:13:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-13/ocampo-withdraws-from-world-bank-contest-portafolio-reports.html
Jose Antonio Ocampo, a former
Colombian finance minister, has withdrawn his candidacy to
become the next World Bank president because he lacks support
for the job, Bogota-based newspaper Portafolio  reported today ,
citing a letter written by the economist.  Ocampo now supports the candidacy of  Nigeria 's Finance Minister
Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala over U.S. nominee Jim Yong Kim, the newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
